    "shortDescription": "Raccoon dogs are the only wild dogs that hibernate — not deeply, but enough to sleep through the coldest winter weeks curled up in a den, living off their fat reserves. Their raccoon-like face mask is just a coincidence: they're actually canids, more closely related to foxes than to raccoons. Fun fact: Raccoon dogs are the only dog family members that regularly climb trees."
